# Use make.ps1 Targets - No Freelance Commands

## ZERO DISCRETION POLICY

If a `make.ps1` target exists for an operation, use it. No exceptions.
Do not substitute a raw `npm`, `npx`, `tsc`, `eslint`, `prettier`, or `vitest`
command when a make target wraps it - even for a "quick" check.

## Why this matters

`./make.ps1 test` runs `npm run rebuild:node` via the `pretest` npm lifecycle hook
before invoking vitest. This rebuilds `better-sqlite3` for the correct Node.js
ABI (Electron vs system Node.js differ). Bypassing the make target skips the
rebuild and causes native module ABI mismatch errors.

The same logic applies to other targets: they may run setup steps, enforce
ordering, or apply flags that a raw command would miss.

## Required substitutions

| Never use this | Use this instead |
|---|---|
| `npx vitest run` | `./make.ps1 test` or `./make.ps1 test-fast` |
| `npx vitest run --coverage` | `./make.ps1 test` |
| `tsc --noEmit` | `./make.ps1 type-check` |
| `tsc --build` | `./make.ps1 arch-check` |
| `eslint .` | `./make.ps1 lint` (runs full suite) |
| `prettier --check .` | `./make.ps1 lint` (runs full suite) |
| `prettier --write .` | `./make.ps1 format` |
| `drizzle-kit generate` | `./make.ps1 migration` |
| `drizzle-kit migrate` | `./make.ps1 db-upgrade` |
| `electron-vite dev` | `./make.ps1 dev` |
| `electron-vite build` | `./make.ps1 build` |

## When a raw command IS acceptable

Only when there is no make target for the operation - for example:
- `git` commands (no make target)
- `npm install` (no make target)
- Inspecting a specific file or running a one-off script not covered by make

## Full target reference

```powershell
./make.ps1 test        # vitest run --coverage (enforces thresholds) + rebuild
./make.ps1 test-fast   # vitest run (no coverage, faster) + rebuild
./make.ps1 test-e2e    # playwright
./make.ps1 test-all    # test + test-e2e
./make.ps1 lint        # tsc + arch-check + eslint + prettier
./make.ps1 arch-check  # tsc --build: layer contract enforcement
./make.ps1 type-check  # tsc --noEmit only
./make.ps1 format      # prettier --write + eslint --fix
./make.ps1 dev         # electron-vite dev
./make.ps1 build       # electron-vite build + electron-builder
./make.ps1 migration   # drizzle-kit generate + rebuild:node
./make.ps1 db-upgrade  # drizzle-kit migrate + rebuild:node
```
